HEADWORD: Keitloa
<hw>Keit*lo"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A black, two-horned, African
rhinoceros (<spn>Atelodus keitloa</spn>). It has the posterior horn
about as long as the anterior one, or even longer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

